  <section id="home">
    <h2>Home</h2>
    <p>Welcome to the official tribute site of Presley Chweneyagae, a talented actor, leader, and inspiration to many across South Africa and the world.</p>
  </section>

  <section id="about">
    <h2>About Presley Chweneyagae</h2>
    <p>Presley Chweneyagae was born on October 19, 1984, in Mafikeng, South Africa. He rose to fame after starring in the 2005 film <em>Tsotsi</em>, which won an Oscar for Best Foreign Language Film. He also played major roles in <em>The River</em>, <em>iNumber Number</em>, and <em>90 Plein Street</em>.</p>
    <p>He was not only an actor but also a mentor and community leader through the Presley Chweneyagae Foundation.</p>
  </section>

  <section id="achievements">
    <h2>Achievements</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Lead role in Oscar-winning film <strong>Tsotsi</strong> (2005)</li>
      <li>Starred in <strong>The River</strong> as Cobra Mokoena</li>
      <li>Won Golden Horn Award for Best Actor</li>
      <li>Acted in <em>Mandela: Long Walk to Freedom</em> and <em>Zama Zama</em></li>
      <li>Founded the Presley Chweneyagae Foundation</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

